cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with deep feature tensors and their compression, which are commonly used in computer vision applications such as object detection. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves compression techniques, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of neural networks and deep learning also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves prediction schemes, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
